getHeaderValue

public java.lang.String getHeaderValue()
Return the value(s) of the header as a semi-colon separated string. For example, if your values are "foo", "bar" and "baz" this will return the string "foo; bar; baz"

Returns:
the string encoded reprsentation of the header values suitable for insertion into a HTTP request

getRawHeaderValue

public java.lang.String getRawHeaderValue()
Return a raw header value (i.e., before any processing/splitting). If the header was mentioned multiple times, this method returns all the header values concatenated together and separated by a comma (RFC 2616, Section 4.2 Message Headers: "It MUST be possible to combine the multiple header fields into one (..) without changing the semantics of the message, by appending each subsequent field-value to the first, each separated by a comma").

Returns:
a single string that contain the raw header values concatenated together, separated by a comma
